Actor Aremu Afolyan has lamented the declining exchange rate of the naira. The actor, who has been in Dubai, was shocked to realise N1m could only get him 6025 Dirham’s. The pained actor wrote: “Guys, how are you? I mean, Nigeria is so dead, I mean dead. I will show you why it’s dead because if the economy of a country is not growing, then it is a burial ground.   I’ve never felt insecure about my body –…     Jaro Davids dedicates ‘Obong of Sankwala’ to Obanliku LG     ICYMI: I need a complete man for urgent marriage –…   “Let me show you the money first before I tell you what I will suggest. “6025 Dirham is N1 million. “Oye ki gbogbo citizen Nigeria ko kuro ni ( let every citizen in Nigeria leave)”